<br>
If I die and need a res, I first check the zone I'm in.  If a cleric is there, I ask politely for a res (and apologise for asking), and offer to pay his/her asking price, as well as drag corpse to a spot that is convenient.  If the answer is no, I thank him/her politely for their time and move on.  If I have to ask someone in another zone, I offer LARGE payments (I've offered as much as 500pp, and one person my brother was grouped with offered 2500 -unbelievable, huh?).  Most times Im fine with eating the exp loss, however, some times I will search until I find a willing cleric who wants the cash, or has the time to be nice <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   An example of this was at any time during level 46.  It is a killer to die in 46 (and I assume 51 as well).  The exp loss, and the time required to get the exp back is nasty, and I'm short on time, so am willing to pay the plat.  Sorry to all the clerics for the interruptions, but my cleric friends aren't always online <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   As soon as I have my SK up in the 50's I may start a cleric just to increase the number of clerics on Luclin <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> </font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#F5F5DC><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon2.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ulieah.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lieah</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verda